Years of focus and expertise have led to the Starbucks Roast Spectrum. Each coffee bean requires a unique balance of temperature and time to reach its individual peak of aroma, acidity, body and flavor.

Starbucks Blonde Roast

Medium Roast

FAQ

How do I store ground coffee?

An opened bag of coffee is highly perishable, just like fresh produce. Store your beans in an airtight container at room temperature for no longer than a week. The trick is to keep it away from oxygen, light, heat and moisture as much as possible.

How much ground coffee should I use per cup?

The recipe for great coffee is 2 tbsp. (10 g) of freshly ground coffee for every 6 fl. oz. (180 mL) of water. Keep this proportion consistent no matter how much you’re brewing. If the results are too strong for your taste, add hot water to your brewed coffee. Using less coffee will create a bitter cup.

Flavor Name:Breakfast Blend  |  Size:20 Ounce (Pack of 1)

Starbucks Breakfast Blend medium-roast coffee is a shade lighter than most of our offerings—more toasty than roasty—and is the result of playing with roast and taste profiles together for a flavor that appealed to a wider range of palates. Perfect if you want to wake up to a less-intense coffee but still want a lot of character; it's lively with a citrusy tang that gives way to a clean finish. Stock up now for the holiday season so you can share your favorite coffee with visitors or as gifts for coffee lovers.

How does Amazon calculate star ratings?
Amazon calculates a product’s star ratings based on a machine learned model instead of a raw data average. The model takes into account factors including the age of a rating, whether the ratings are from verified purchasers, and factors that establish reviewer trustworthiness.
